                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_english">
                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            Venus, one of the closest planets to Earth in the solar system, is also one of our closest neighbors. Like Earth, Venus is a rocky planet, but due to its close proximity to the Sun, its surface temperature is extremely high, reaching around 400 degrees Celsius.

                            During the night, Venus shines brightly in the sky, similar to the Moon on Earth. In the night sky, Venus is brighter than other celestial bodies, making it easy to spot. Moreover, when Venus is close to Earth, we can even see its surface features and cloud formations with the naked eye.

                            Venus's surface is filled with volcanoes and mountains, as well as various types of cloud formations. In Venus's atmosphere, there are thick clouds of carbon dioxide and sulfuric acid. These clouds reflect sunlight, making Venus's surface appear shrouded in a thick mist.

                            Furthermore, Venus has a very slow rotation, with its rotation period longer than its orbital period. This means that a day on Venus is equivalent to 88 Earth days, while a year is only about 225 Earth days. This also means that both daytime and nighttime on Venus are very prolonged.

                            With its extremely high surface temperature and lack of liquid water, Venus is unlikely to support the existence of life. However, Venus remains a mysterious planet worthy of exploration and understanding for humans.

                            Now, children can go to sleep peacefully and have sweet dreams. We hope you have a wonderful tomorrow!
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-collapseEarth">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapseEarth" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapseEarth">
                    地球(Earth)
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="flush-collapseEarth" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="flush-collapseEarth" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="spell_zhuyin">
                        <h5>ZhuYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            從很久很久以前，地球就開始了它的冒險之旅。它從宇宙中的一個小小的點開始，逐漸變得越來越大，越來越複雜，直到現在的模樣。

                            這一路上，地球經歷了很多挑戰和變化。有時它被猛烈的風暴和自然災害所襲，有時又被溫暖的陽光和清新的空氣所包圍。但無論發生什麼事情，地球總是能夠承受並且繼續前進。

                            在這個晚上，當地球準備休息時，它停下了所有的活動，讓自己沉浸在安寧的氛圍中。星星閃耀著，月亮照亮了整個大地，所有的生物都安靜地入睡了。

                            在這樣的氛圍下，地球開始回顧它的冒險旅程。它想起了過去的一切，那些美好的時光和困難的時刻，它都一一回味著。然後，地球決定要感謝所有支持它的生物，讓它得以繼續前進。

                            於是，地球開始發出溫暖的能量，向每一個在夜晚醒著的生物送去它的感激之情。從大洋深處的小魚，到高山深處的老熊，地球的愛與感激之情瀰漫在每一個角落。

                            當地球把它所有的感激都表達完後，它進入了深深的沉睡狀態。但是，它的愛和感激之情卻在整個夜晚中繼續發酵，瀰漫在每一個角落，保護著每一個生物。

                            所以，當你今晚入睡時，請記得，地球是多麼強大和神奇的存在，它的愛和感激之情，會一直陪伴著你，保護你，直到你醒來的那一刻。晚安
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_pingyin">
                        <h5>PingYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            從很久很久以前，地球就開始了它的冒險之旅。它從宇宙中的一個小小的點開始，逐漸變得越來越大，越來越複雜，直到現在的模樣。

                            這一路上，地球經歷了很多挑戰和變化。有時它被猛烈的風暴和自然災害所襲，有時又被溫暖的陽光和清新的空氣所包圍。但無論發生什麼事情，地球總是能夠承受並且繼續前進。

