                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            A long time ago, in a small village on Mars, there lived a little Martian named Beibei. Beibei likes the stars and the sun very much. Every night, she would lie on the window sill to observe the stars, and the first thing she would do every morning was to run to the window to watch the sun.

                            One night, Beibei saw a very bright star in the sky. He was very excited, because this was a star he had never seen before, and he wanted to know the name of this star very much.

                            So Beibei ran to ask his friends, but no one knew the name of the star. Beibei was very disappointed. He wanted to know the name of the star, but he couldn't find the answer.

                            The next morning, Beibei came to the window again and looked at the sun in the sky. Suddenly, he noticed a tiny black spot in the sky, which gradually grew larger until it became a tiny spaceship. Beibei was very excited, he knew that this must be a friend from an alien.

                            The spaceship landed in the garden of Beibei's house, and a little alien came out of the ship. He told Beibei that this bright star was called "Princess Mars", and this alien came from Princess Mars. Here he is on a mission to find one of the smartest little Martians and help them solve a puzzle.

                            Beibei was very excited, he decided to help the alien and successfully solved the problem. The aliens are very grateful to Beibei, and they look at Princess Mars together and enjoy the beautiful starry sky.

                            From that day on, Beibei became the most popular little Martian in the Martian village. They observed the stars and shared their stories together every night. Most importantly, they learned a lot about the stars and the sun from the aliens, which made them love this beautiful planet even more.

                            Beibei and his friends gathered together under the starry sky, lying on the ground and looking up at the sky. Their eyes were fixed on the bright stars, as if they had endless stories to tell.

                            One of the children asked, "Are there children on Mars like us, looking up at the sky?"

                            Another child replied, "Of course! But the stars they see may not be the same as we see."

                            The third child asked curiously, "Why?"

                            "Because the positions of Mars and the Earth are different, the positions of the stars seen at different times will be different." The child who answered explained.

                            A little girl said, "I want to hear a story about the stars on Mars."

                            So, everyone began to listen to the little girl tell the story about the stars of Mars. She told about a special star on Mars called "Fire Star".

                            "The red star does not twinkle like other stars, it always shines with a warm glow. Some people say that there is a group of elves living on the red star, and they illuminate the whole planet with red light, making Mars full of life and vitality."

                            After listening to the story, the children found it very interesting, and they wanted to know more about the mysterious things on Mars. 
                            
                            They all expressed that they wanted to become future Mars explorers and explore every corner of this mysterious planet.
                        </p>
