                    <div class="spell_english">
                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            Jupiter is the largest planet in the solar system, larger than all the other planets combined. From Earth, Jupiter appears a pale yellow color, but in the night sky, it appears as a very bright object.

                            Jupiter's surface is made of gaseous matter, so it doesn't have a solid surface like Earth. In Jupiter's atmosphere, there are many storms and clouds, the most famous of which is the Great Red Spot storm. One of the most famous celestial bodies in the solar system, the Great Red Spot has been around for hundreds of years, longer than human history.

                            Jupiter is also a planet with many moons, the most famous of which are the Galilean moons. The Galileo satellite is the first satellite discovered in human history. Its surface is full of craters and mountains, and it also has many canyon-like landforms on the earth.

                            In addition to the Galilean moons, Jupiter has many other moons. Recently, NASA's Juno probe successfully entered Jupiter's orbit in 2016 and began to conduct detailed detection and research on Jupiter.

                            Jupiter is a mysterious and beautiful planet that rediscovers the vastness and infinite possibilities of our solar system. Now, children can sleep peacefully and have sweet dreams. I hope you will have a better tomorrow!
                        </p>
                    </div>

