                            At one point, the children of Uranus got into an argument with Aphrodite, one of the Earth goddesses, because they thought she was too conceited. Uranus did not want these quarrels to disrupt the harmony among the gods, so he decided to end their quarrels by banishing his children deep underground.

                            This made Uranus' wife, Gaia, very angry, and she thought it was unfair. So she conspired with her grandson Cronus (Cronus) to help Cronus replace Uranus and make him the new god of the sky.

                            Uranus was banished for a long time, but eventually he was freed. He was very grateful to the gods who helped him and decided to give them some special gifts. He gave Aeolus the power over the winds, Poseidon the sea god, and Hephaestus the fire of technology to man.

