                            Neptune, the furthest planet in the solar system from the sun, has a surface made of gas and ice. Unlike other planets, Neptune has very intense storms in its atmosphere, the most famous of which is the Great Dark Spot. This huge storm has existed for decades, and its size can even cover the entire earth.

                            Neptune's moons are also very special, the most famous of which is the <code>Triton</code> moon. The surface of <code>Triton</code> is filled with craters and mountains, the most famous of which is Tiger Volcano. The material erupted from this volcano is so special that it looks like a pink cloud due to the reflection of sunlight.

