                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            The science stories are also very interesting when it comes to Pluto. Here's a science story about Pluto:

                            Pluto was originally considered the ninth planet, but in 2006 it was reclassified as a "dwarf planet," a decision made by the International Astronomical Union.

                            Pluto is considered one of the smallest planets in the solar system, measuring only one-fifth the diameter of Earth. It is located at the edge of the solar system, about 5.9 billion kilometers from the sun.

                            The temperature on the surface of Pluto is very cold, usually between -229°C and -223°C. Its surface is also covered in layers of icy nitrogen, methane and some icy carbon. Pluto's atmosphere is very thin, consisting of nitrogen and methane, but it only evaporates when the planet is close to the sun.

                            Pluto has five known moons, the largest being Charon. Charon's surface is also covered in icy material, but some mountains and valleys have also been found.

                            Pluto is difficult to study because it is so far away from Earth and other planets in the solar system affect its orbit. However, scientists have still managed to obtain a lot of important information about Pluto through long-distance observations and the launch of space probes.
                        </p>
                    </div>


                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingCeres">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapseCeres" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapseCeres">
                    穀神星(Ceres)
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="flush-collapseCeres" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="flush-headingCeres" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="spell_zhuyin">
                        <h5>ZhuYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            豐收女神 (Ceres)：豐收女神是太陽系中最大的矮行星，也是太陽系內第一顆被發現的矮行星。它於1801年被義大利天文學家朱塞佩·皮亞齊發現，
                            並以羅馬神話中的豐收女神得以命名。豐收女神的直徑約為940公里，它主要由岩石和冰組成，被認為是一顆古老的天體，可能擁有類似地球的水冰資源。

                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_pingyin">
                        <h5>PingYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            豐收女神 (Ceres)：豐收女神是太陽系中最大的矮行星，也是太陽系內第一顆被發現的矮行星。它於1801年被義大利天文學家朱塞佩·皮亞齊發現，
                            並以羅馬神話中的豐收女神得以命名。豐收女神的直徑約為940公里，它主要由岩石和冰組成，被認為是一顆古老的天體，可能擁有類似地球的水冰資源。
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_english">
                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            Ceres: Ceres is the largest dwarf planet in the solar system and the first dwarf planet discovered in the solar system. It was discovered by Italian astronomer Giuseppe Piazzi in 1801.
                            And named after the harvest goddess in Roman mythology. The goddess of harvest is about 940 kilometers in diameter. It is mainly composed of rock and ice.
                            It is considered to be an ancient celestial body and may have water ice resources similar to the earth.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingEris">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapseEris" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapseEris">
                    鬩神星(Eris)
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="flush-collapseEris" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="flush-headingEris" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="spell_zhuyin">
                        <h5>ZhuYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            赫米斯 (Eris)：赫米斯是太陽系中最大的已知矮行星之一，於2005年被美國天文學家麥可·布朗和他的團隊發現。
                            赫米斯的直徑約為2326公里，被認為比冥王星還要大。赫米斯的名字來自希臘神話中的紛爭之神厄里斯，象徵著這顆天體的爭議性質。
                            赫米斯的軌道非常遠離太陽，它的公轉周期超過550年，並且被認為可能是來自外太空的一顆天體。
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_pingyin">
                        <h5>PingYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            赫米斯 (Eris)：赫米斯是太陽系中最大的已知矮行星之一，於2005年被美國天文學家麥可·布朗和他的團隊發現。
                            赫米斯的直徑約為2326公里，被認為比冥王星還要大。赫米斯的名字來自希臘神話中的紛爭之神厄里斯，象徵著這顆天體的爭議性質。
                            赫米斯的軌道非常遠離太陽，它的公轉周期超過550年，並且被認為可能是來自外太空的一顆天體。
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_english">
                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            Hermes (Eris): Hermes is one of the largest known dwarf planets in the solar system, discovered in 2005 by American astronomer Michael Brown and his team.
                            With a diameter of about 2326 km, Hermes is thought to be larger than Pluto. Hermes takes its name from Eris, the god of strife in Greek mythology, and symbolizes the controversial nature of the celestial body.
                            Hermes orbits very far from the sun, has a revolution period of more than 550 years, and is thought to be a possible object from outer space.
                        </p>
                    </div>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header" id="flush-headingHaumea">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapseHaumea" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapseHaumea">
                    妊神星(Haumea)
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="flush-collapseHaumea" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="flush-headingHaumea" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <div class="spell_zhuyin">
                        <h5>ZhuYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            海曼娜是太陽系中的一顆橢圓形矮行星，於2004年被西班牙天文學家和他的團隊發現。
                            海曼娜的形狀非常特殊，呈現出類似綿羊棒的形態，因此被暱稱為「綿羊狀矮行星」。
                            海曼娜的直徑約為1960公里，並且以夏威夷神話中的生育之神海曼娜命名。
                            海曼娜的表面被認為可能覆蓋著冰和岩石，並且可能擁有一個相對年輕的衛星。
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_pingyin">
                        <h5>PingYin</h5>
                        <p>
                            海曼娜是太陽系中的一顆橢圓形矮行星，於2004年被西班牙天文學家和他的團隊發現。
                            海曼娜的形狀非常特殊，呈現出類似綿羊棒的形態，因此被暱稱為「綿羊狀矮行星」。
                            海曼娜的直徑約為1960公里，並且以夏威夷神話中的生育之神海曼娜命名。
                            海曼娜的表面被認為可能覆蓋著冰和岩石，並且可能擁有一個相對年輕的衛星。
                        </p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="spell_english">
                        <h5>English</h5>
                        <p>
                            Hymana is an elliptical dwarf planet in the solar system, discovered in 2004 by the Spanish astronomer and his team.
                            Hymana has a very special shape, showing a shape similar to a sheep rod, so it is nicknamed the "sheep-shaped dwarf planet".
                            Haimana has a diameter of about 1960 kilometers and is named after Haimana, the fertility god in Hawaiian mythology.
                            Hymana's surface is thought to be likely covered in ice and rock, and may host a relatively young moon
                        </p>
                    </div>

